# Laravel Backend Rules — Bunyan

## Directory Structure

```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── Enums/              # PHP enums (UserRole, ProjectStatus)
│   ├── Http/
│   │   ├── Controllers/    # Thin — delegate to services
│   │   ├── Middleware/      # Auth, RBAC
│   │   ├── Requests/       # Form Request validation
│   │   └── Resources/      # API Resources
│   ├── Models/             # Eloquent models
│   ├── Services/           # Business logic layer
│   ├── Repositories/       # Database access layer
│   ├── Policies/           # Authorization policies
│   ├── Events/
│   ├── Listeners/
│   ├── Jobs/
│   ├── Notifications/
│   └── Enums/
├── database/
│   ├── migrations/
│   ├── seeders/
│   └── factories/
├── routes/api.php
├── config/
├── resources/lang/ (ar/, en/)
└── tests/ (Unit/, Feature/)
```

## Patterns

### Controller Pattern (Thin)

```php
class ProjectController extends Controller
{
    public function __construct(private ProjectService $service) {}

    public function store(StoreProjectRequest $request)
    {
        $project = $this->service->create($request->validated());
        return new ProjectResource($project);
    }
}
```

### Service Pattern (Business Logic)

```php
class ProjectService
{
    public function __construct(private ProjectRepository $repository) {}

    public function create(array $data): Project
    {
        // Business logic here — no HTTP, no direct Eloquent
        return $this->repository->create($data);
    }
}
```

### Repository Pattern (Data Access)

```php
class ProjectRepository
{
    public function create(array $data): Project
    {
        return Project::create($data);
    }
}
```

### Form Request Validation

```php
class StoreProjectRequest extends FormRequest
{
    public function authorize(): bool
    {
        return $this->user()->can('create', Project::class);
    }

    public function rules(): array
    {
        return [
            'name' => ['required', 'string', 'max:255'],
            'description' => ['nullable', 'string'],
        ];
    }
}
```

## Eloquent Rules

- Always eager load relationships to prevent N+1
- Use `select()` to limit columns
- Use query scopes for reusable conditions
- Use chunking for large datasets
- Index columns used in WHERE, ORDER BY, JOIN
- Use `utf8mb4` charset for Arabic text

## Migration Rules

- File naming: `YYYY_MM_DD_HHMMSS_verb_noun_table.php`
- Verbs: `create`, `add`, `modify`, `drop`, `rename`
- Always include `down()` method
- Never modify existing migrations
- Soft deletes on: users, projects, phases, tasks, products, orders
- Audit columns: `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`

## API Rules

- Prefix: `/api/v1/`
- Use plural nouns: `/api/v1/projects`
- Nested for ownership: `/api/v1/projects/{project}/phases`
- Laravel API Resources for response formatting
- Pagination: `?per_page=`, `?page=`, `?sort=`, `?filter[field]=`

## Security

- Authentication: Laravel Sanctum
- Authorization: Policies and Gates
- Input validation: Form Request classes
- File uploads: validate MIME type, size server-side
- No raw queries with user input

